data.name: AMP Bank Term Deposit
data.description: Lock in a great rate and know what you'll earn with deposits starting at $5,000, plus pay no monthly fees.

fees.name: Cheque or electronic withdrawal dishonour fee
fees.additionalInfo: When a cheque or electronic withdrawal from your account is dishonoured

fees.name: Cheque deposit or electronic payment dishonour fee
fees.additionalInfo: When a cheque deposited to your account is dishonoured, or an electronic payment initiated from your account is sent back from a financial institution

fees.name: Bank cheque fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to: issue a bank cheque, provide a replacement bank cheque for one previously issued, repurchase a bank cheque you no longer require,arrange to make a bank cheque available for you to collect from a Westpac branch. Interest payable on the bank cheque amount from the day the request is processed by us.

fees.name: International ATM cash withdrawal fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you withdraw from your account at any international ATM

fees.name: Currency conversion fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you use your access card to make a purchase overseas or withdraw from an ATM overseas in a foreign currency and the transaction is converted to Australian dollars

fees.name: Deposit special clearance fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to expedite the clearance of a cheque deposited to your account

fees.name: Duplicate statement fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request a copy of a previously provided statement to be sent to you by mail

fees.name: Emergency replacement Access Card fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request urgent delivery of a replacement access card

fees.name: Telegraphic transfer fee - deposits
fees.additionalInfo: When funds are transferred to your account (by SWIFT or telegraphic transfer) from a bank in Australia or overseas (in Australian dollars)

fees.name: Telegraphic transfer fee - withdrawals
fees.additionalInfo:
When you request us to transfer funds from your account (by SWIFT) to a bank in Australia (in Australian dollars)
When you request us to transfer funds from your account (by telegraphic transfer) to an overseas bank (in Australian dollars or a foreign currency).

fees.name: Foreign currency draft fee - issued
fees.additionalInfo: When you request a draft (cheque) to be issued in a foreign currency

fees.name: Foreign currency draft fee - stop
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to place a 'stop' on a foreign currency draft that has not yet been presented for payment

fees.name: Foreign currency draft fee - deposit
fees.additionalValue: On receipt plus overseas bank fee
fees.additionalInfo: When a foreign currency draft (cheque) is received and deposited to your account from overseas and must be converted into Australian dollars

fees.name: Transaction trace fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to investigate and trace a transaction

fees.name: Visa dispute fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you dispute a Visa transaction and we do not find in your favour

fees.name: Audit certificate fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you or an auditor request an audit certificate for your account

features.additionalValue: Access is available to online banking features for the product

constraints.additionalInfo: Minimum Term Deposit is $5000 for terms of 3 months and more
Balances over $5,000,000 are available at our discretion.
